body:
**Description of the issue** 
I have an SRAM design which is 8 rows deep and 8 bits wide. I am stitching up the 2 instances to obtain an SRAM that is 8 rows deep and 16 bits wide.  I have instantiated 2 instances of the same module (sram_top). When I try to build the simulation (from RTL to c++ and makefiles), it builds successfully. But when I try to run it (make V{top_module_name}) , it throws "Active region did not converge" error. **But when I instantiate just one instance of the SRAM module (sram_top), the simulation runs correctly without the active region did not converge error .**

Code snippet for the code I am working with,
The module "sram_top1" is described in another file which is included in this file (using a `include). I have also instantiated this module "top_sram_wrapper" in a stimulus file which provides it clk_i and rst.
 
```
module top_sram_wrapper (
input clk_i,
input rn,
output reg done_read 
);
integer i;

reg done_write = 1'b0;
reg done = 1'b0;
reg dvdd = 1'b1;
reg dvss = 1'b0;

reg cs = 1'b0;
reg we = 1'b0;
reg [3:0] addr_temp;
reg [2:0] addr;
reg [3:0] wmask;
wire [31:0] wdata;
reg [31:0] d_out;

wire [7:0] d_in_0, d_in_1, d_in_2, d_in_3; 
wire [7:0] d_out_0, d_out_1, d_out_2, d_out_3;
reg csb_col0, csb_col1, csb_col2, csb_col3;
reg [31:0] mem [0:511];

// Display the signals 
  always @ (posedge clk_i) begin
        $display("Time: %0t | clk_i: %b | rst_ni: %b | addr_a: %b | mem_value: %h | a_wmask: %b | !we: %b", $time, clk_i, rn, addr, wdata, ~wmask, !we);
  end

// Loading the BRAM with program memory
  initial begin
    $display("Loading ram.");
    $readmemh("hello_test.vmem", mem);
    for  (i=0; i<512; i++) $display("%h",mem[i]);
    $display("BRAM loaded successfully");
  end

// generating address for writing and reading
  always @(posedge clk_i or negedge rn) begin
       if (!rn) begin
         wmask = 4'b0000;
         addr = 3'b0;
         cs = 0;
         we = 0;
         addr_temp = 0;
       end
       else begin
        if (!done) begin
            if (addr_temp == 4'b1000) begin
                done = 1;
            end
            else begin
                addr_temp = addr_temp + 1'b1;
                addr = addr_temp-1;
            end
        end
       end
  end

// Checking the simulation conditions  
 always @(posedge clk_i or negedge rn) begin
   if (rn) begin
    if (done && !done_write) begin
        $display("Write over...");
        done_write = 1'b1;
        done = 1'b0;
        addr = 3'b0;
        addr_temp = 0;
    end
    else if (done && done_write) begin
        $display("Read over...");
        done_read = 1'b1;
        done = 1'b0;
        addr = 3'b0;
        addr_temp = 0;
    end
    else begin
       if (!done_write) begin
         wmask = 4'b1111;
         cs = 1;
         we = 1;
       end
       else begin 
        wmask = 4'b1111;
        cs = 1;
        we = 0;
       end              
    end
   end
  end

assign wdata = mem[addr];

assign d_out[7:0] = d_out_0;
assign d_out[15:8] = d_out_1;
assign d_out[23:16] = d_out_2;
assign d_out[31:24] = d_out_3;
assign csb_col0 = !wmask[0];
assign csb_col1 = !wmask[1];
assign csb_col2 = !wmask[2];
assign csb_col3 = !wmask[3];
assign d_in_0 = wdata [7:0];
assign d_in_1 = wdata [15:8];
assign d_in_2 = wdata [23:16];
assign d_in_3 = wdata [31:24];

sram_top1 I1 (
.addr(addr), 
.d_in(d_in_0), 
.d_out(d_out_0), 
.clk(clk_i), 
.csb(csb_col0), 
.dvdd(dvdd), 
.dvss(dvss), 
.rn(rn), 
.web(!we)
);
sram_top1 I2 (
.addr(addr), 
.d_in(d_in_1), 
.d_out(d_out_1), 
.clk(clk_i), 
.csb(csb_col1), 
.dvdd(dvdd), 
.dvss(dvss), 
.rn(rn), 
.web(!we)
);
endmodule

```
**The errors are shown below** 
```
-V{t1,1}         'act' region trigger index 1 is active: @([hybrid] arails_top.x_390.control_unit.pre_buf_chain.INV_5.a_y)
-V{t1,2}         'act' region trigger index 35 is active: @([changed] arails_top.x_390.SRAM_Bank.VcellinptDummy_Replica_1__bl or [changed] arails_top.x_390.SRAM_Bank.VcellinptDummy_Replica_1__br or [changed] arails_top.x_390.SRAM_Bank.Dummy_Replica_1.replica_bitcell_rbl_wl.drive_mode or [changed] arails_top.x_390.rbl_wl)
-V{t1,3}         'act' region trigger index 36 is active: @([changed] arails_top.x_390.Port.port_addr.Vcelloutdecoder_wl0__y1 or [changed] arails_top.x_390.SRAM_Bank.VcellinptDummy_Replica_1__bl or [changed] arails_top.x_390.SRAM_Bank.VcellinptDummy_Replica_1__br or [changed] arails_top.x_390.SRAM_Bank.Dummy_Replica_1.replica_bitcell_wl1.drive_mode)
-V{t1,4}         'act' region trigger index 37 is active: @([changed] arails_top.x_390.Port.port_addr.Vcelloutdecoder_wl0__y0 or [changed] arails_top.x_390.SRAM_Bank.VcellinptDummy_Replica_1__bl or [changed] arails_top.x_390.SRAM_Bank.VcellinptDummy_Replica_1__br or [changed] arails_top.x_390.SRAM_Bank.Dummy_Replica_1.replica_bitcell_wl0.drive_mode)
-V{t1,5}         'act' region trigger index 38 is active: @([changed] arails_top.x_390.Port.port_addr.Vcelloutdecoder_wl0__y6 or [changed] arails_top.x_390.SRAM_Bank.VcellinptDummy_Replica_0__br or [changed] arails_top.x_390.SRAM_Bank.Dummy_Replica_0_2.replica_cell_1.drive_mode or [changed] arails_top.x_390.Vcellinpcontrol_unit__rbl_bl)

%Error: dut_verilog/arails_top_module.v:1: Active region did not converge.

```
**The command used** 
verilator -cc --exe -O2 -x-assign 0 -Wall  -Wno-ENUMVALUE --trace --assert --coverage -Wno-fatal --timing --relative-includes --top-module arails_top -f input.vc dut_verilog/arails_top.v sim_main.cpp

The verilator version is "Verilator 5.026 2024-06-15 rev v5.026"

**What OS ?**
Cent OS 7 

It would be great if you could please assist me in coming up with a fix for this problem.
